# Clerk auth routing

This app does **not** have a dedicated sign-in or sign-up **page** (no `/sign-in` or `/sign-up` routes as the primary auth entry). Sign-in and sign-up are exposed from the **homepage** (`/`) and the global header (Clerk in modal mode with shadcn controls, per the shadcn UI rules).

## Requirements

- When unauthenticated users must be turned away from a **protected** route (Server Components, layouts, or middleware), send them to the **homepage** with `redirect("/")` (or the app’s configured home path), **not** to `/sign-in`, `/sign-up`, or other “login page” URLs.
- Do not implement or document “redirect to the sign-in page” as the default unauthenticated flow for this project.

## Disallowed patterns

- `redirect("/sign-in")`, `redirect("/sign-up")`, or equivalent, as the standard gate for protected content when the product uses homepage-based auth.
- Assuming Clerk hosted **page** routes at `/sign-in` / `/sign-up` exist in this codebase unless they are explicitly added later.

## Preferred pattern

```tsx
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { redirect } from "next/navigation";

export default async function ProtectedPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) redirect("/");
  // ... load user-scoped data
}
```
